String Compression
String Compression is a technique used to reduce the size of a string by replacing consecutive repeated characters with:
the character + followed by the number of times it appears consecutively.
String Compression means counting consecutive repeated characters and replacing them with character + count.
Example - 
aabbc
a2b2c1
Why do we use String Compression?
Suppose we have a string containing many repeated characters.
Instead of storing lengthy string - aaaaabbbbcccc
we can store -
a5b4c4
This saves space (when there are many repeated characters).

